PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study investigated whether the manner in which conflicts are resolved in Japanese-American joint ventures in Japan influences the level of future mutual trust. Japanese managers perceived a higher level of future trust when disputes are resolved through conferral, except when an American is in charge of operations. Then they designated contracts requiring binding arbitration.
AB  - This study investigated whether the manner in which conflicts are resolved in Japanese-American joint ventures in Japan influences the level of future mutual trust. Japanese managers perceived a higher level of future trust when disputes are resolved through conferral, except when an American is in charge of operations. Then they designated contracts requiring binding arbitration.
